solution: ```class Solution {
    public int minSwaps(String s) {
        int openNeeded = 0;
        int closeSeen = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '[') {
                if (closeSeen > 0) {
                    closeSeen--;
                }
            } else {
                closeSeen++;
                openNeeded = Math.max(openNeeded, (closeSeen + 1) / 2);
            }
        }
        return openNeeded;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Track the number of unmatched closing brackets; each pair of unmatched closers requires one swap. The formula (closeSeen + 1) / 2 gives the minimal swaps needed to balance the prefix.

